{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.38",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 38,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 38",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 38 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:1",
      "text": "Then the Lord answered Job out of the whirlwind, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:2",
      "text": "Who is this that darkeneth counsel by words without knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:3",
      "text": "Gird up now thy loins like a man; for I will demand of thee, and answer thou me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:4",
      "text": "Where wast thou when I laid the foundations of the earth? declare, if thou hast understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:5",
      "text": "Who hath laid the measures thereof, if thou knowest? or who hath stretched the line upon it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:6",
      "text": "Whereupon are the foundations thereof fastened? or who laid the corner stone thereof;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:7",
      "text": "When the morning stars sang together, and all the sons of God shouted for joy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:8",
      "text": "Or who shut up the sea with doors, when it brake forth, as if it had issued out of the womb?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:9",
      "text": "When I made the cloud the garment thereof, and thick darkness a swaddlingband for it,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:10",
      "text": "And brake up for it my decreed place, and set bars and doors,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:11",
      "text": "And said, Hitherto shalt thou come, but no further: and here shall thy proud waves be stayed?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:12",
      "text": "Hast thou commanded the morning since thy days; and caused the dayspring to know his place;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:13",
      "text": "That it might take hold of the ends of the earth, that the wicked might be shaken out of it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:14",
      "text": "It is turned as clay to the seal; and they stand as a garment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:15",
      "text": "And from the wicked their light is withholden, and the high arm shall be broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:16",
      "text": "Hast thou entered into the springs of the sea? or hast thou walked in the search of the depth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:17",
      "text": "Have the gates of death been opened unto thee? or hast thou seen the doors of the shadow of death?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:18",
      "text": "Hast thou perceived the breadth of the earth? declare if thou knowest it all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:19",
      "text": "Where is the way where light dwelleth? and as for darkness, where is the place thereof,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:20",
      "text": "That thou shouldest take it to the bound thereof, and that thou shouldest know the paths to the house thereof?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:21",
      "text": "Knowest thou it, because thou wast then born? or because the number of thy days is great?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:22",
      "text": "Hast thou entered into the treasures of the snow? or hast thou seen the treasures of the hail,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:23",
      "text": "Which I have reserved against the time of trouble, against the day of battle and war?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:24",
      "text": "By what way is the light parted, which scattereth the east wind upon the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:25",
      "text": "Who hath divided a watercourse for the overflowing of waters, or a way for the lightning of thunder;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:26",
      "text": "To cause it to rain on the earth, where no man is; on the wilderness, wherein there is no man;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:27",
      "text": "To satisfy the desolate and waste ground; and to cause the bud of the tender herb to spring forth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:28",
      "text": "Hath the rain a father? or who hath begotten the drops of dew?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:29",
      "text": "Out of whose womb came the ice? and the hoary frost of heaven, who hath gendered it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:30",
      "text": "The waters are hid as with a stone, and the face of the deep is frozen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:31",
      "text": "Canst thou bind the sweet influences of Pleiades, or loose the bands of Orion?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:32",
      "text": "Canst thou bring forth Mazzaroth in his season? or canst thou guide Arcturus with his sons?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:33",
      "text": "Knowest thou the ordinances of heaven? canst thou set the dominion thereof in the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:34",
      "text": "Canst thou lift up thy voice to the clouds, that abundance of waters may cover thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:35",
      "text": "Canst thou send lightnings, that they may go, and say unto thee, Here we are?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:36",
      "text": "Who hath put wisdom in the inward parts? or who hath given understanding to the heart?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:37",
      "text": "Who can number the clouds in wisdom? or who can stay the bottles of heaven,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.38",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:38",
      "text": "When the dust groweth into hardness, and the clods cleave fast together?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.39",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:39",
      "text": "Wilt thou hunt the prey for the lion? or fill the appetite of the young lions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.40",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:40",
      "text": "When they couch in their dens, and abide in the covert to lie in wait?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.38.41",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:41",
      "text": "Who provideth for the raven his food? when his young ones cry unto God, they wander for lack of meat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
